pageContext.claim: “As a young man, he captained the Yale baseball team, and then went on to serve as the youngest aviator in the United States Navy during the Second World War.”
pageContext.analysis: In his prepared statement on the death of former President George H.W. Bush, Trump unaccountably reversed the order of two key moments in Bush's life. Bush enlisted in the Navy on his 18th birthday and then only went to Yale after the war ended.
